Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
-Flagship 8,556 SF Restaurant Retail opportunity in the heart of the Union Market District

-Signal House, once completed, will be an eleven-story trophy office building located in the Union Market neighborhood of Washington, D.C. adjacent to Florida Avenue and less than a five-minute walk from the NOMAGallaudet Metro Station. Designed by Gensler, the 225,000 RSF project will pay tribute to its historically industrial surroundings with a truly unique terracotta, metal, and glass exterior.

-Signal House will feature some of the tallest ceiling heights and widest column spacing in the city. In addition, Signal House will offer private terraces, a windowed conference center, state-of-the-art fitness facilities, below-grade parking, secure bike storage, 11,000 SF of premium retail, and a rooftop boasting a DJ booth, karaoke room, kitchen, bar, and breathtaking views of the Capitol.
